Subject: Re: [T2] bottom cooling housing flaps

I don't have the little flappers, and I understand that you probably don't
need them if you don't have or use the blower (I live in Sand Diego). I
guess it wouldn't really hurt to run the blower without them; I just don't
think you'd get any more airflow than with just the main cooling fan.

You should use the cover plates though; otherwise you probably wouldn't get
any heat up front, and you might reduce engine cooling flow. Use something
to seal them up nice and tight.

RickG
'77 Westy "Pumpkin II"
