<SNIP>
What do these flaps do and do I really need 'em? My guess is that when the
heater fan is on and the car is idling, it keeps hot air from blowing back
into the cooling fan housing. I would assume that during higher RPMs, the
cooling fan air pressure high is enough to overcome the heater fan pressure
and direct the air away from the cooling housing. Sound logical?
